name: The Baris Memedi Dance ( Tengkudak )
description:
Symbols in Balinese culture are articulated through art, like through the dance movements.
A work of dance depicting local beliefs. The Baris Memedi Dance which was held in Tengkudak Village, Penebel District, Tabanan Regency. 
This dance is played before the Pitra Yadnya Ceremony ( Balinese Cremation Ceremony ). This dance has its own character. There are 7 to 9 dancers, including 1 Penemprat.
